#: ../../contributing/html.rst:14
msgid ""
"All HTML documents must use **two spaces** for indentation and there should "
"be no trailing whitespace. XHTML syntax must be used (this is more a Genshi "
"requirement) and all attributes must use double quotes around attributes. ::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../contributing/html.rst:23
msgid ""
"HTML5 elements should be used where appropriate reserving ``<div>`` and "
"``<span>`` elements for situations where there is no semantic value (such as"
" wrapping elements to provide styling hooks)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../contributing/html.rst:29
msgid "Doctype and layout"
msgstr ""

#: ../../contributing/html.rst:31
msgid ""
"All documents must be using the HTML5 doctype and the ``<html>`` element "
"should have a ``\"lang\"`` attribute. The ``<head>`` should also at a "
"minimum include ``\"viewport\"`` and ``\"charset\"`` meta tags. ::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../contributing/html.rst:47
msgid "Forms"
msgstr ""

#: ../../contributing/html.rst:49
msgid ""
"Form fields must always include a ``<label>`` element with a ``\"for\"`` "
"attribute matching the ``\"id\"`` on the input. This helps accessibility by "
"focusing the input when the label is clicked, it also helps screen readers "
"match labels to their respective inputs. ::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../contributing/html.rst:57
msgid ""
"Each ``<input>`` should have an ``\"id\"`` that is unique to the page. It "
"does not have to match the ``\"name\"`` attribute."
msgstr ""

#: ../../contributing/html.rst:60
msgid ""
"Forms should take advantage of the new HTML5 input types where they make "
"sense to do so, placeholder attributes should also be included where "
"relevant. Including these can provided enhancements in browsers that support"
" them such as tailored inputs and keyboards. ::"
msgstr ""

